column7: Q1 = Do you use any social media?
column8: Q2 = Which social media account do you use mostly?
column9: Q3 = On average, how much time do you spend on social media daily?
column10: Q4 = What is the main reason for using social media?
column11: Q5 = Approximately how many follower do you have across all social media account?
column12: Q6 = On average , how many photos ,videos,posts or reels do you share on social media montly?
column13: Q7 =  I remind myself that others only share highlights  on social media, but I still compare my real life to their curated posts?
column14: Q8 = Looking at old posts of myself or other makes me feel like I am not progressing as I should
column15: Q9 = When I see about others posts about achievements or experiences I think about how my life could have been different if I had those opportunities
column16: Q10 = I feel left out when I see friends post about events I wasn't invited to
column17: Q11 =l often compare myself with others with respect to what l have accomplished in life
column18: Q12 = I have bought things that were too expensive for me just to fit in with my friends.
column19: Q13 =I act like I enjoy activities my friends like, even if I don't actually enjoy them.
column20: Q14 = I feel pressure to goto parties or hangouts with friends, even when I need to study them.
column21: Q15 =.l've changed how Iook( (like hairstyle or clothing) to match the style of other students in my engineering group.
column22: Q16 =  I feel pressure to choose a career or internship that's similar to what my friends are doing.
column23: Q17 = I question whether the skills I'm learning in my subjects will matter in my career.
column24: Q18 = I've become less enthusiastic about solving assignment problems or participating in practical classes
column25: Q19 =  Attending lectures or practicals feels emotionally exhausting.
column26: Q20 =  I sometimes doubt if I can keep up with everything in my engineering program.
column27: Q21 =  l feel mentally drained after working on assignments or projects?.
column28: Q22 =  I am happy with the amount of time I spend connecting with friends or participating in social activities.
column29: Q23 = I am satisfied with the progress that am making toward my academic and career goals.
column30: Q24 = I feel good about my choices in my engineering journey so far.
column31: Q25 =  Overall, I am satisfied with the life as an engineering student.
column32: Q26 =  I am satisfied with the balance between academic work and hobbies or personal interests.
column33: Q27 = Most of the time, I have meals without company.
column34: Q28 = I feel lonely on weekends when I'm not busy with classes.
column35: Q29 = I don't feel happy when I keep everything to myself.
column36: Q30 =  I feel as if nobody understands me.
column37: Q31 = I feel like an outsider in my engineering department, even whensurrounded by peers.
column38: Q32 = I have friends who enjoy spending time with me.
column39: Q33 = When I'm feeling down, I have at least one family member I can talk to about anything
column40: Q34 =  My close friends actively remind me that social media posts are highlight reels, not reality.
column41: Q35 = My support network celebrates my small wins.
column42: Q36 = My family makes me feel valued for who I am.
